            <fr:addr type="user">hmlg-001E</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>hmlg-001E.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Perturbation of the smaller chain complex in a chain reduction"><fr:link href="hmlg-001C.xml" title="Perturbation of chain complex" addr="hmlg-001C" type="local">Perturbation</fr:link> of the smaller chain complex in a <fr:link href="hmlg-0017.xml" title="Chain reduction" addr="hmlg-0017" type="local">chain reduction</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Construction</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Given a reduction <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho  : C \Rightarrow \mkern {-14mu}\Rightarrow  D]]></fr:tex> and a perturbation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _D]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>, we can construct a perturbation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _C]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>, such that the same <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho ]]></fr:tex> can serve as a reduction of the perturbed chain complexes.</fr:p>
  
    
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="trebor.xml" title="Trebor" addr="trebor" type="local">Trebor</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>26</fr:day></fr:date><fr:source-path>/Users/trebor/Desktop/blog/forest/trees/hmlg-001E.tree</fr:source-path><fr:anchor>1607</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/461</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-461.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Let the reduction <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho ]]></fr:tex> be made out of the three maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi _{\rho } : C \to  D]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\iota _{\rho } : D \to  C]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h_{\rho } : C \to  C]]></fr:tex>. Then since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> splits as the direct sum of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> and an <fr:link href="hmlg-000D.xml" title="Acyclic chain complex" addr="hmlg-000D" type="local">acyclic</fr:link> complex, we can simply copy over the perturbation, and leave the acyclic part untouched. This gives us the definition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _C = \iota _{\rho } \mathbin {\circ } \delta _D \mathbin {\circ } \pi _{\rho }]]></fr:tex>. A quick computation shows that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho ]]></fr:tex> is still a reduction of the perturbed chain complexes.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
  
